acdSmap.description: The Service mapping database for this Accedian Networks device.

acdSmapCoSProfTable.name: acdSmapCoSProfTable
acdSmapCoSProfTable.description: The CoS profile table. Each row in the table represents a CoS Profile. A CoS profile is used to map an input packet to an L2 class of service. This traffic mapping (classification) is accomplished using one of the following fields in the incoming packet: p-bits in 802.1Q / 802.1Q-in-Q tags IP precedence bits in IPv4 TOS byte DSCP bits in IPv4 DSCP byte The class of service value (0-7) assigned to the outgoing traffic is selected based on the conformance level (Green/Yellow) of the incoming traffic. The following sections describe the general configuration parameters and the mapping table of a CoS profile.

acdSmapCoSProfEntry.name: acdSmapCoSProfEntry
acdSmapCoSProfEntry.description: An entry consisting of all settings to manage a CoS profile.

acdSmapCoSProfID.name: acdSmapCoSProfID
acdSmapCoSProfID.description: Unique value for each CoS Profile instance.

acdSmapCoSProfRowStatus.name: acdSmapCoSProfRowStatus
acdSmapCoSProfRowStatus.description: All columns must have a valid value before a row can be activated. To create a new CoS Profile you shall provide the a unique name and the type for an empty row with the RowStatus set to Create and Go. To delete the CoS Profile you need to set the RowStatus to destroy.

acdSmapCoSProfName.name: acdSmapCoSProfName
acdSmapCoSProfName.description: This is a string to uniquely identify the CoS profile.

acdSmapCoSProfType.name: acdSmapCoSProfType
acdSmapCoSProfType.description: Indicates the type of CoS profile. Possible values are: PCP, IP precedence or DSCP.

acdSmapCoSProfDecodeDropBit.name: acdSmapCoSProfDecodeDropBit
acdSmapCoSProfDecodeDropBit.description: This field is only valid for PCP CoS profiles. If this field is set, the pre-marking color is decoded from the DEI bit (Drop Eligible Indication). Otherwise, the user defined pre-color is used.

acdSmapCoSProfEncodeDropBit.name: acdSmapCoSProfEncodeDropBit
acdSmapCoSProfEncodeDropBit.description: This field controls the DEI bit in an S-VLAN tag. If this field is set and the outgoing packet is marked yellow then the DEI bit is set to 1. Otherwise, the DEI is set to 0.

acdSmapCoSProfCodePointTable.name: acdSmapCoSProfCodePointTable
acdSmapCoSProfCodePointTable.description: The Configuration table of all code point entries. Each row in the table represents a Code point. the number of code points depend of the acdSmapCoSProfType value. p-bits in 802.1Q / 802.1Q-in-Q tags IP precedence bits in IPv4 TOS byte DSCP bits in IPv4 DSCP byte The class of service value (0-7) assigned to the outgoing traffic is selected based on the conformance level (Green/Yellow) of the incoming traffic.

acdSmapCoSProfCodePointEntry.name: acdSmapCoSProfCodePointEntry
acdSmapCoSProfCodePointEntry.description: An entry consisting of all settings for a code point.

acdSmapCoSProfCodePointID.name: acdSmapCoSProfCodePointID
acdSmapCoSProfCodePointID.description: Unique value for each row. Base on Code Point, 0 to 63 for DSCP or 0 to 7 for PCP or IP precedence.

acdSmapCoSProfCodePointPreMarkingColor.name: acdSmapCoSProfCodePointPreMarkingColor
acdSmapCoSProfCodePointPreMarkingColor.description: This is the user pre-color to mark the incoming traffic. This field is only valid if acdSmapCoSProfDecodeDropBit is not set.

acdSmapCoSProfCodePointGreenOut.name: acdSmapCoSProfCodePointGreenOut
acdSmapCoSProfCodePointGreenOut.description: The class of service value that will be used in the outgoing green packets. This value is selected if the result of the bandwidth regulator assigned to this entry is green or if the pre-marking color is green and no bandwidth regulator is assigned to this entry.

acdSmapCoSProfCodePointYellowOut.name: acdSmapCoSProfCodePointYellowOut
acdSmapCoSProfCodePointYellowOut.description: The class of service value that will be used in the outgoing yellow packets. This value is selected if the result of the bandwidth regulator assigned to this entry is yellow or if the pre-marking color is yellow and no bandwidth regulator is assigned to this entry.

acdSmapRegSetTable.name: acdSmapRegSetTable
acdSmapRegSetTable.description: The Regulator Set profile table. Each row in the table represents a Regulator Set. A bandwidth regulator set allows the user to regulate traffic based on the following information: p-bits in 802.1Q / 802.1Q-in-Q tags IP precedence bits in IPv4 TOS byte DSCP bits in IPv4 DSCP byte.

acdSmapRegSetEntry.name: acdSmapRegSetEntry
acdSmapRegSetEntry.description: An entry consisting of all settings to manage a Regulator set.

acdSmapRegSetID.name: acdSmapRegSetID
acdSmapRegSetID.description: Unique value for each Regulator set instance.

acdSmapRegSetRowStatus.name: acdSmapRegSetRowStatus
acdSmapRegSetRowStatus.description: All columns must have a valid value before a row can be activated. To create a new Regulator set you shall provide the a unique name and the type for an empty row with the RowStatus set to Create and Go. To delete the CoS Profile you need to set the RowStatus to destroy.

acdSmapRegSetName.name: acdSmapRegSetName
acdSmapRegSetName.description: This is a string to uniquely identify the Regulator set.

acdSmapRegSetType.name: acdSmapRegSetType
acdSmapRegSetType.description: Indicates the type of Regulator Set. Possible values are: PCP, IP precedence or DSCP.

acdSmapRegSetCodePointTable.name: acdSmapRegSetCodePointTable
acdSmapRegSetCodePointTable.description: The Configuration table of all code point entries. Each row in the table represents a Code point. the number of code points depend of the acdSmapCoSProfType value. p-bits in 802.1Q / 802.1Q-in-Q tags; IP precedence bits in IPv4 TOS byte; DSCP bits in IPv4 DSCP byte.

acdSmapRegSetCodePointEntry.name: acdSmapRegSetCodePointEntry
acdSmapRegSetCodePointEntry.description: An entry consisting of all settings for a code point.

acdSmapRegSetCodePointID.name: acdSmapRegSetCodePointID
acdSmapRegSetCodePointID.description: Unique value for each row. Base on Code Point, 0 to 64 for DSCP or 0 to 7 for PCP or IP precedence.

acdSmapRegSetCodePointRegulatorID.name: acdSmapRegSetCodePointRegulatorID
acdSmapRegSetCodePointRegulatorID.description: The bandwidth regulator that will be used to regulate the traffic flow that has this PCP/IP precendence/DSCP value. Refer to acdRegulatorTable to find the exact identifier (same as acdRegulatorID).

acdSmapRegSetCodePointRegulatorEnable.name: acdSmapRegSetCodePointRegulatorEnable
acdSmapRegSetCodePointRegulatorEnable.description: Enable or disable traffic regulation for this PCP, IP precedence or DSCP value.

acdSmapCoSProfGroup.name: acdSmapCoSProfGroup
acdSmapCoSProfGroup.description: Objects for the CoS profile Group.

acdSmapCoSProfCodePointGroup.name: acdSmapCoSProfCodePointGroup
acdSmapCoSProfCodePointGroup.description: Objects for the CoS profile CodePoint Group.

acdSmapRegSetGroup.name: acdSmapRegSetGroup
acdSmapRegSetGroup.description: Objects for the Regulator Set Group.

acdSmapRegSetCodePointGroup.name: acdSmapRegSetCodePointGroup
acdSmapRegSetCodePointGroup.description: Objects for the Regulator Set CodePoint Group.
